{
  "reasoning": {
    "cause": "The car repeatedly deployed more energy than it could recover, especially in early laps, leading to a net energy deficit.",
    "consequence": "This caused a progressive drop in State of Charge (SoC) that limited later deployment options and likely reduced overall lap performance.",
    "recommendation": "Consider reducing early-deployment levels to keep SoC above ~0.7 MJ, or target a higher harvest window in sectors where speed exceeds 340 kph to improve net energy balance.",
    "regulation_citation": {
      "passage": "P(kW) = 250 when the car speed is below 310kph",
      "source": {
        "document_title": "FIA 2026 Formula 1 Technical Regulations — Section C",
        "issue": "Issue 18 — 2026-05-07",
        "section": "C5.2.6",
        "public_url": "https://www.fia.com/regulation/category/110",
        "fetched_at": "2026-05-09T14:11:34.772446Z"
      }
    },
    "confidence": "medium",
    "confidence_justification": "Confidence is medium because the observed SoC trend is clear, but no forecast data is available to predict future laps.",
    "reasoning_chain": [
      "Lap 1 shows a 0.40 MJ harvest followed by a 0.30 MJ deploy, leaving SoC at 0.780 MJ.",
      "Lap 3 harvests only 0.20 MJ while deploying 0.70 MJ, causing SoC to fall to 0.550 MJ – the lowest point observed.",
      "Subsequent laps maintain a higher deploy than harvest, preventing SoC recovery.",
      "Regulation C5.2.6 caps MGU‑K power at 250 kW below 310 kph, meaning early‑lap deployments cannot be compensated by higher power later.",
      "Thus the net energy deficit explains the progressive SoC decline and its impact on performance."
    ]
  },
  "regulation": {
    "chunk_id": "c_053_03",
    "text": "- iii. In the Race or Sprint session on specified circuit sectors, subject to the conditions specified in Article B7.2:\n\nP(kW) = 250 when the car speed is below 310kph\n\nP(kW) = 1800 – 5 * car speed (kph) when the car speed is equal to or above 310kph and below 340kph\n\nP(kW) = 6900 – 20 * car speed (kph) when the car speed is equal to or above 340kph and below 345kph\n\nP(kW) = 0 when the car speed is equal to or above 345kph\n\n- iv. Specific power curves that will be used in Low Grip conditions, the details of which may be found in FIA -F1 -DOC -111.\n\n[FIA] Limbs iii. and iv. are Safety related [FIA] Within the 250KW limited zone, MGU-K deployment would be subject to further modification should clear evidence of any torque delivery concerns be identified.\n\n<!-- image -->",
